SUMMARY:Replay | Accessible by Design: Web Accessibility Essentials for Developers
DESCRIPTION:The Tech Academy\nDidn’t get the chance to tune in live? Here’s your opportunity to watch the replay of this inspiring session with **Brittany Ellich**\, Staff Software Engineer at GitHub\, where she shares key strategies for building accessible and inclusive web experiences.\n\nIn this Talk\, Brittany explores why accessibility matters\, how companies are approaching it\, and practical ways to make websites more inclusive. The session includes hands-on examples of accessible design in action and a look at how AI is transforming the accessibility landscape.\n\nWhether you’re just starting out or looking to enhance your web development skills\, you’ll leave with actionable insights to create better\, more inclusive digital experiences.\n\nSave your spot now and join us on **Friday\\\, March 20 at 1 PM PT \\| 3 PM CT \\| 4 PM ET** to see how accessibility can improve every user’s experience online.
